00:54.466 --> 01:04.336
advertisements is another thing to go on TikTok or on YouTube and see people talk about it, blog about it, walk through the park or even do that first person experience on the ride.

01:04.857 --> 01:07.540
But it is a whole other thing to experience it.

01:07.940 --> 01:11.063
See, that's the difference, of course, between knowing and knowing.

01:11.864 --> 01:13.426
One version of knowing is I know it exists.

01:13.446 --> 01:14.967
Intellectual, yes, it is there.

01:15.388 --> 01:18.191
But real knowing is intellectual and experiential.

01:18.351 --> 01:19.952
That is true knowing.

01:20.173 --> 01:21.554
I half jokingly

01:21.666 --> 01:24.351
posted on Instagram when we were down at Disney.

01:24.411 --> 01:28.218
There are two kingdoms, one that will last and it will never end.

01:28.919 --> 01:30.241
The other will not last.

01:30.882 --> 01:37.194
One gives joy and the other gives momentary happiness, but I am a willful member of both kingdoms.

01:38.236 --> 01:43.205
As many of you know who are here or part of our church, I am a self-proclaimed dysnaholic.

01:43.725 --> 01:46.290
It's rooted in my core memories, of course, as a child.

01:46.530 --> 01:50.636
My parents were missionaries in the 80s in Ecuador every time we would come home back to Canada.

01:50.656 --> 01:52.599
We'd stop in Florida for three plus days.

01:52.639 --> 01:53.420
We'd go to Epcot.

01:53.440 --> 01:54.501
We'd go to Magic Kingdom.

01:54.942 --> 02:01.211
And if you can believe it, I was reflecting on this the other day, they actually used to have discounts for missionaries and pastors.

02:01.912 --> 02:03.695
That day is long gone.

02:04.736 --> 02:07.961
The ones, the rides that form me most, it's a small world.

02:08.081 --> 02:11.045
Peter Pan, figment, of course, at Epcot.

02:11.085 --> 02:12.888
That smell it pirates the Caribbean.

02:12.928 --> 02:14.290
So you know what I'm talking about.

02:14.402 --> 02:18.049
And Mickey himself was embedded in my fabric as a human.

02:18.149 --> 02:19.993
Now, I've passed this on to my family.

02:20.033 --> 02:23.179
Many of you would say, I've infected them with this disease.

02:23.219 --> 02:25.664
Others people like, no, this is the greatest gift you could give them.

02:26.345 --> 02:28.750
But this trip over the summer was a really special moment.

02:28.870 --> 02:34.240
After COVID, we were able, through friends, to get two weeks at a timeshare just beside the parks.

02:35.022 --> 02:37.266
We were really excited to go because

02:37.378 --> 02:40.463
The last time we had gone, Star Wars land didn't even exist.

02:40.523 --> 02:41.945
And there were so many new rides to go.

02:42.205 --> 02:44.068
We're out of two guardians of the galaxy.

02:44.088 --> 02:48.274
And then there's just all the things, the snacks, the ears, all the magic.

02:49.055 --> 02:49.716
But there was a catch.

02:50.718 --> 02:54.083
We were going the last week of July and the first week of August.

02:54.183 --> 02:58.309
And when we told people when we were going, every single person said, you're crazy.

02:59.151 --> 03:00.152
You should not go.

03:00.192 --> 03:02.455
It's so disgusting.

03:02.556 --> 03:03.357
It's so hot.

03:03.397 --> 03:04.178
And we said, no, no.

03:04.354 --> 03:06.257
Yes, yes, we're gonna go and we're gonna be fine.

03:06.537 --> 03:12.325
And we emphatically reminded them and ourselves, it was worth the pain because the lines would be so much shorter.

03:12.966 --> 03:18.915
Well, we went and it was an amazing trip and it was disgustingly hot.

03:19.716 --> 03:25.144
Every day it was somewhere between like 92 and 102 to use American numbers.

03:26.245 --> 03:29.490
The sweat, the smell, the lack of hydration,

03:29.602 --> 03:32.348
The meltdowns, the family fights in line.

03:32.408 --> 03:41.186
Every time it rained, we would put on cheap plastic ponchos, which covered us from the rain, which relieved us, but then suddenly we realized it was so disgusting and humid.

03:41.507 --> 03:47.360
We were now basically walking greenhouses, and we were sweating more underneath than the rain was upon us.

03:48.061 --> 03:48.562
And yet,

03:49.186 --> 03:52.590
The food was amazing and the rides were amazing and the pin trading was amazing.

03:53.030 --> 03:57.796
And exploring Disney with a much less rushed experience was awesome and it was so much fun.

03:58.096 --> 03:58.977
It was magical.

03:59.037 --> 03:59.898
It was immersive.

04:00.198 --> 04:01.339
It was imagination.

04:01.420 --> 04:02.381
It was inspiring.

04:02.441 --> 04:05.484
Our kids actually said it's the best family vacation we ever had.

04:06.385 --> 04:14.514
I remember like in week two looking around at all the good and the great and the bad and the ugly.

04:15.490 --> 04:28.509
and realizing it wasn't just our family, but every single family around us was having the same experiences, amazing and awful and hot and beautiful and joyful and stressful and thoughts like, why in the world are we even here?

04:28.929 --> 04:31.152
And then at the same time, I just cannot wait to come back.

04:31.233 --> 04:32.074
This is incredible.

04:33.676 --> 04:41.227
All of that, to me, is such a vivid, helpful picture for all of us today.

04:41.267 --> 04:43.410
It's a great image, actually, to help us

04:43.650 --> 04:47.114
talk about reality when actually knowing God in Christ.

04:47.875 --> 04:52.580
Not just the amazing good but the difficult and the terrible, all in one experience.

04:54.242 --> 04:55.163
More on that in a moment.

04:56.185 --> 05:01.030
As we end this amazing summer series on the names of God, we of course end with Jesus.

05:01.050 --> 05:11.122
And if again, you're a seeker here today or skeptic or a cultural Christian or you belong to another form of faith or you're spiritual in general, by the end of this talk,

05:12.002 --> 05:14.825
You'll know the fullness of actually what Jesus claimed about himself.

05:14.865 --> 05:19.109
You'll be able to say yes, no, or I'm not sure in a very informed way.

05:19.910 --> 05:33.863
Now for others of us who have already said yes, that is we know Jesus, believe in Jesus and follow Jesus, we will by the end of the sermon be able to see him, more love him, more be thankful, inspired, faithful, and hopefully inspired with more hope.

05:34.925 --> 05:40.530
Now in the book of John, Jesus seven times said I am and then used an image.

05:41.122 --> 05:42.364
He said, I am the bread of life.

05:43.205 --> 05:44.306
I am the light of the world.

05:45.287 --> 05:45.928
I am the gate.

05:46.068 --> 05:47.009
I am the good shepherd.

05:47.049 --> 05:48.331
I am the resurrection in the life.

05:48.431 --> 05:50.273
I am the way, the truth and the life.

05:50.414 --> 05:51.335
I am the true vine.

05:51.515 --> 05:57.302
And so to end our names of God series, I want to speak to that great Old Testament name, I am.

05:57.342 --> 06:07.475
And as we get to that name and its connection to Jesus, I want to walk us through the story in the place where Jesus said, I am the bread of life.

06:08.937 --> 06:10.098
It's all about food.

06:10.818 --> 06:14.184
There's an obvious thing about food I preached out of John six years ago here.

06:14.684 --> 06:16.908
And I said, we don't reflect on this very much, but it's true.

06:16.928 --> 06:19.112
Food, once it's eaten, is gone.

06:19.472 --> 06:20.715
And of course, we get hungry again.

06:20.815 --> 06:29.169
I said, imagine the best meal you could ever have, like Michelin star, five star, crazy amount of money, hundreds of thousand dollars.

06:29.509 --> 06:32.154
And it's like, oh my goodness, and a McDonald's drive through.

06:33.055 --> 06:34.698
The experiences are profoundly different.

06:35.259 --> 06:37.202
And the quality might be profoundly different.

06:37.890 --> 06:40.053
But at the end of the day, the food is the same fate.

06:40.233 --> 06:42.737
It goes into your stomach and then some of it into the toilet.

06:42.757 --> 06:44.119
It's here today and it's gone tomorrow.

06:45.401 --> 06:46.483
And here's the point.

06:47.945 --> 06:49.487
We want lasting things.

06:49.567 --> 06:51.230
We search, we long for eternity.

06:51.510 --> 06:52.592
Those things that are eternal.

06:52.652 --> 06:59.743
And actually, this is one reason why Jesus truly came to His day and in our day to show us the emptiness of life.

07:00.183 --> 07:02.066
Jesus wants to free us, to show us.

07:02.178 --> 07:06.964
much of the time how defective our view of life and existence and eternity really are.

07:07.285 --> 07:10.228
He actually claims that he comes to give food from heaven.

07:10.569 --> 07:19.981
He has come to reveal who he actually is and what he wants to give and both never run out and both are amazing promises and yet they have to be rooted in the names of God.

07:20.922 --> 07:22.164
Now, we're going to be in John 6.

07:22.184 --> 07:25.488
So you've got a Bible, physical copy or online somewhere.

07:25.508 --> 07:27.250
Would you just flip to John 6?

07:28.546 --> 07:32.652
This passage begins with Jesus feeding the 5,000, which isn't actually 5,000.

07:32.672 --> 07:34.574
That's just the men that were counted.

07:34.594 --> 07:36.196
So this is way over 10,000 people.

07:37.058 --> 07:40.642
And he feeds them with two sardines and five large crackers.

07:41.784 --> 07:44.748
And this was setting the stage for his claim that he is food that never runs out.

07:44.848 --> 07:49.735
So after he feeds thousands in the most miraculous of ways, Jesus just gets up and he leaves.

07:50.416 --> 07:58.066
The crowd is so epically blown away from this act, they hunt Jesus down and demand more from him.

07:58.914 --> 08:10.972
The crowd, like many of us, when we get close to Jesus, we begin to have all sorts of experiences at once, just like that Disney story, beautiful and disgusting and hot and awesome.

08:11.533 --> 08:15.979
When people got close to Jesus, they get confused and angry and shocked and encouraged.

08:17.041 --> 08:23.270
Jesus tells them they have to trust in Him only, not in what they do, and actually not what they want.

08:24.271 --> 08:26.034
Verse 26, I tell you the truth.

08:26.978 --> 08:31.983
You're looking for me, not because you saw miraculous signs, but because you ate your loaves and had your fill.

08:32.003 --> 08:34.566
You are so earthly motivated.

08:34.887 --> 08:40.713
Jesus is going to again and again try to move this massive crowd away from what they just experienced alone.

08:41.514 --> 08:44.958
The stuff you bake, the stuff you buy at the grocery store won't last.

08:45.138 --> 08:47.560
Simple truth, you need food, you eat it, it's gone.

08:48.221 --> 08:50.083
If you don't eat it and it sits there, it rots.

08:50.884 --> 08:51.625
It just doesn't last.

08:52.506 --> 08:56.370
Physical food satisfies for a moment, but the spiritual food

08:56.578 --> 08:59.903
that I'm offering actually lasts and it must come from God.

09:00.824 --> 09:11.921
Then Jesus says this in verse 27, do not work for food that spoils, but for food that endures to eternal life, which the Son of Man will give you on him, God the Father's place, his seal of approval.

09:12.001 --> 09:16.247
Okay, Jesus says, look, I'm going to give you something way more than bread.

09:17.429 --> 09:18.951
You have to trust in me and only me.

09:19.072 --> 09:19.292
Why?

09:19.392 --> 09:23.779
Because God the Father, Elohim Yahweh, the God of the Old Testament, has put his steel on me.

09:23.979 --> 09:24.840
Well, what's that?

09:24.940 --> 09:26.002
Well, that's the Holy Spirit.

09:26.402 --> 09:29.325
The Holy Spirit is given to Jesus at his baptism.

09:29.685 --> 09:31.167
And at that moment, two things take place.

09:31.207 --> 09:33.569
Number one, God the Father declares, this is my son.

09:34.690 --> 09:38.214
And also Jesus at that moment is empowered for ministry.

09:39.075 --> 09:41.877
And Jesus is gonna say, I've got God's backing in approval.

09:43.619 --> 09:52.388
And then in verse 28, the crowd asked one of the most important questions in the whole Bible, but actually it's the question that's asked by billions of people today.

09:53.208 --> 09:54.770
What must we do

09:55.842 --> 10:00.208
What must we do to do the work God requires?

10:00.228 --> 10:02.111
What kind of work do we need to do to get this bread?

10:03.072 --> 10:03.833
What must I give?

10:03.913 --> 10:04.614
What must I do?

10:04.995 --> 10:07.438
What do I need to bring the table to get this eternal stuff?

10:08.019 --> 10:09.481
What good works must I do?

10:09.621 --> 10:11.244
What things must I do to please God?

10:11.284 --> 10:12.786
How much credit do I need to build up?

10:13.887 --> 10:17.472
Because you're talking about things that seem pretty epic and amazing, and I want them.

10:17.492 --> 10:19.014
How much is this going to cost me?

10:19.135 --> 10:24.402
On the surface, of course, this question seems right and expected.

10:24.514 --> 10:26.276
And the question is deeply religious.

10:26.316 --> 10:33.627
How good, how religious, and Jesus undercuts all of it and says, actually, you've already already got this wrong.

10:34.327 --> 10:34.548
What?

10:36.010 --> 10:40.256
Verse 29, the work of God is this, to believe in the one He sent.

10:43.100 --> 10:46.965
This undercuts almost every religious worldview on earth, like that.

10:48.166 --> 10:50.770
I've used this example, I think twice before, I want to read it again.

10:51.202 --> 10:54.987
One person reflecting on this said, they asked what kind of work they had to do to get bread.

10:55.968 --> 10:58.592
Jesus responds by saying, there is no physical work you can do.

10:59.373 --> 11:00.815
You need to believe in Jesus.

11:01.556 --> 11:04.039
The bread that lives or endures comes through faith.

11:04.360 --> 11:05.401
Suppose, I love this.

11:05.521 --> 11:09.707
Suppose you invite a family over for Sunday afternoon dinner.

11:10.768 --> 11:11.369
It's a great meal.

11:12.210 --> 11:13.452
You put on a huge spread for them.

11:14.033 --> 11:15.074
You fix their favorite meat.

11:15.094 --> 11:16.115
Cook it just the way they like.

11:16.135 --> 11:21.042
There's a big toss green salad, steaming baked potatoes, cheese sauce, refreshing beverage.

11:21.154 --> 11:21.815
Apple pie.

11:22.576 --> 11:24.338
Now, by the way, I love our church.

11:24.358 --> 11:26.360
We've got probably 55 plus nationalities.

11:26.820 --> 11:29.864
And that's a very, very traditional sort of North American dish.

11:30.404 --> 11:35.951
You think about the best meal in your cultural setting that you would serve to a guest, whatever that might be.

11:37.272 --> 11:37.873
What a dinner.

11:39.415 --> 11:45.221
Soon, ever in sitting back, padding full tummies and suppose it's time for your guests to leave.

11:46.082 --> 11:49.426
And they take it their wallets and they ask you, how much do we owe you for this meal?

11:50.274 --> 11:52.876
You would probably say, you don't owe me anything.

11:53.817 --> 11:55.599
But wonder if your friends or guests respond.

11:55.619 --> 11:57.281
We absolutely do owe you something.

11:57.561 --> 11:58.882
We're not freeloaders.

11:59.703 --> 12:00.544
How much do we owe you?

12:00.624 --> 12:04.127
And then take out like two or $320 bills and throw them on the table.

12:04.527 --> 12:11.534
Just the mention of payment in this setting would be like such a grievous insult to you, let alone throwing the money.

12:11.874 --> 12:12.595
And then he writes this.

12:12.715 --> 12:20.242
And yet, do we not find ourselves going through life trying to pay for a free meal

12:20.962 --> 12:23.625
and in the process always insulting God, whole.

12:25.547 --> 12:26.208
Let me read this again.

12:26.248 --> 12:37.740
The work of God is this, believe in the one he has sent so that they ask him, what miraculous sign will you give that we may see it and believe you?

12:37.780 --> 12:39.802
What will you do, Jesus?

12:40.643 --> 12:46.510
See, our forefathers, eight men in the desert, as it's written in the Old Testament, he gave them bread from heaven to eat.

12:47.050 --> 12:48.111
Yeah, Jesus, okay.

12:49.092 --> 12:50.514
Thanks for yesterday.

12:50.914 --> 12:54.343
And that was amazing, but we moved on and don't get us wrong again.

12:54.604 --> 12:59.317
Yesterday was pretty amazing, but we now need you to do one better.

12:59.578 --> 13:02.265
So let's see you match or beat the big guy.

13:03.268 --> 13:03.950
Match Moses.

13:04.732 --> 13:05.554
I mean, I dare you.

13:05.986 --> 13:08.550
Remember Jesus before you say you can do all this.

13:08.890 --> 13:10.493
We want to remind you, I mean, you're here to you.

13:10.513 --> 13:16.682
So you know this too, that, you know, Moses fed Israel six days a week for 40 years with bread from heaven.

13:16.742 --> 13:19.786
You fed 10,000 of us with one meal.

13:19.906 --> 13:24.012
So we want you to give us a sign that's more significant than Moses.

13:24.353 --> 13:28.158
And that's going to assure us of this permanent sign of bread.

13:29.240 --> 13:30.141
Well, Jesus then does it.

13:30.602 --> 13:33.426
He says in verse 35, he says, I'm the bread of life.

13:34.434 --> 13:36.857
He who comes to me will never go hungry.

13:36.877 --> 13:38.759
He who believes in me will never be thirsty.

13:39.620 --> 13:40.081
It's me.

13:40.141 --> 13:42.284
You all are missing this.

13:43.245 --> 13:44.326
It's not the miracles.

13:44.847 --> 13:46.729
The miracles point to the miracle giver.

13:47.170 --> 13:47.830
I'm the food.

13:48.351 --> 13:50.554
I'm the substance that will nourish body and soul.

13:50.634 --> 13:50.974
It's me.

13:51.475 --> 13:52.516
Listen, it's no mistake.

13:52.556 --> 13:53.517
I was born in Bethlehem.

13:53.537 --> 13:54.218
You all know this.

13:54.459 --> 14:01.267
Bethlehem literally means house of bread, even the place where I was born points to not only who I am, but why I've come.

14:01.527 --> 14:03.730
I am the bread

14:04.130 --> 14:04.631
of life.

14:06.213 --> 14:08.878
Now notice, they keep talking about Moses.

14:09.559 --> 14:16.189
So just since we're, make sure that we're on the same page, the people of God leave Egypt and they're on their way to the promised land.

14:17.030 --> 14:19.855
And there's a lot of detours for 40 years, but they're in trouble.

14:20.676 --> 14:21.297
They had no food.

14:21.337 --> 14:22.099
They cry out to God.

14:22.159 --> 14:29.330
And then in Exodus 16, it reads like this, the Israelites said to Moses in the leadership, we'd only died by God's hand in Egypt.

14:30.114 --> 14:36.982
There we set our own pots of meat and ate all the food we wanted, but you have brought us into this desert to starve this entire assembly to death.

14:37.803 --> 14:42.549
Verse 4, God said to Moses, I will rain down bread from heaven for you.

14:43.430 --> 14:48.196
Verse 15, Moses said to them, it is the bread the Lord has given you to eat.

14:48.797 --> 14:52.281
Verse 31, the people in Israel called this bread manna.

14:52.942 --> 14:56.306
It was white like coriander seed and tasted like wafers made with honey.

14:56.930 --> 15:04.522
Now, an original Jewish person hearing Jesus would have been like totally blown away by this statement.

15:04.542 --> 15:05.844
Because this is what Jesus is saying.

15:05.944 --> 15:09.009
Jesus is saying, I'm manna from heaven.

15:09.049 --> 15:10.591
Me.

15:11.833 --> 15:13.716
That physical thing is fulfilled in me.

15:14.016 --> 15:15.178
Another person wrote it like this.

15:16.060 --> 15:18.303
Manna typified Jesus.

15:19.305 --> 15:20.867
For it is white like snow.

15:21.508 --> 15:23.812
Just like Jesus is without blemish or imperfection.

15:24.172 --> 15:25.394
Manna's accessible.

15:25.634 --> 15:27.237
That's actually one of the main virtues.

15:27.678 --> 15:30.924
A person could walk outside of the camp to gather it, but they had a choice.

15:31.004 --> 15:36.996
They could either walk on it or pick it up so we can either walk by or walk on Jesus or take him up as Savior.

15:37.116 --> 15:37.797
What do you want?

15:39.040 --> 15:40.242
He knows the heart of the crowd.

15:40.883 --> 15:44.750
It says in verse 36, but as I told you, you have seen me and you still don't believe.

15:45.732 --> 15:46.674
You've seen me.

15:46.786 --> 15:47.487
You just saw me.

15:47.527 --> 15:48.248
Some of you were there.

15:48.328 --> 15:52.312
I fed like 10,000 plus people with five crackers and two sardines.

15:52.572 --> 15:53.693
You've seen me heal the sick.

15:53.713 --> 15:54.934
You've seen me cast out demons.

15:54.954 --> 15:56.156
You've seen me raise the dead.

15:56.436 --> 15:57.737
You've heard my teaching.

15:58.058 --> 16:00.020
You've said time and time and time again.

16:00.080 --> 16:03.103
We've never heard someone teach God's truth like this.

16:03.163 --> 16:05.465
So clearly such power, such authority.

16:05.706 --> 16:10.731
We've never heard anyone talk like this or do these things, but you still don't believe.

16:11.852 --> 16:13.714
But then Jesus says, ah, but some of you will.

16:15.138 --> 16:16.980
All that the Father gives me will come to me.

16:17.961 --> 16:19.983
And whoever comes to me, I will never drive away.

16:20.884 --> 16:28.032
For I have come down from heaven, not to do my will, but to do the will of Him who sent me."

16:28.052 --> 16:34.139
See salvation here again, undercutting all humanism, all self-reliance, every religious system.

16:34.559 --> 16:38.483
Salvation is by God, for God, and through God alone.

16:39.404 --> 16:42.107
We never come to Jesus because we think it's a good idea.

16:42.988 --> 16:44.690
Jesus is not a good idea.

16:45.538 --> 16:50.025
For people who are deeply in dark practices, they don't want to be exposed.

16:50.065 --> 16:53.110
People that are self-sufficient, they don't want to admit that doesn't help.

16:53.571 --> 17:03.686
Listen, it doesn't matter where you come from, secular, spiritual, religious or not, because when Jesus shows up, we all have to be honest about pride, sin and our true condition.

17:03.727 --> 17:06.871
See, the sovereign grace of God, that's how we come to believe.

17:06.992 --> 17:08.454
We don't talk ourselves into faith.

17:08.794 --> 17:09.796
It's not of our own doing.

17:10.097 --> 17:11.058
He brings us to life.

17:12.866 --> 17:22.220
verse 39, this is the will of Him who sent me, that I shall lose none of all that He gives me, but raise them up on the last day.

17:22.561 --> 17:29.592
For my Father's will is that every who looks to the Son and believes in Him will have eternal life, and I will raise them up on the last day.

17:30.974 --> 17:39.026
When you actually stop and hear Jesus' words plainly like that, what Jesus said right there is so damning and so powerful

17:39.394 --> 17:43.279
And so shocking and so encouraging, depending on what you do with Jesus.

17:44.380 --> 17:49.507
For those that embrace Jesus, it's eternal life and there's purpose and Jesus will never leave us and he'll never drive us away.

17:49.867 --> 17:56.095
We'll never go hungry and thirsty in the ultimate sense because our deepest need to know God and enjoy him forever will be fulfilled.

17:57.097 --> 17:57.878
Death doesn't win.

17:57.918 --> 18:02.083
He actually says he's physically going to bring us back from the dead, just like of course, what happened to him.

18:02.404 --> 18:04.606
But if you don't choose him, you don't get any of this.

18:06.329 --> 18:07.410
Well, verse 41.

18:07.554 --> 18:09.597
The crowd begins to turn.

18:10.297 --> 18:14.843
At this, the Jews began to grumble about him because he said, I am the bread that came down from, oh, heaven.

18:17.126 --> 18:19.629
They're no different than their ancestors and we're no different than them.

18:20.871 --> 18:23.714
God moved, of course, and saved and provided in the desert.

18:23.854 --> 18:25.977
And they didn't like how or where or when it happened.

18:25.997 --> 18:27.078
And once again, they're not pleased.

18:27.098 --> 18:32.525
Now what they're hearing in this moment, they start getting angry, they complain, and it's here they really begin to object.

18:33.506 --> 18:36.530
They want Jesus on their own terms, not on his terms.

18:37.186 --> 18:37.947
Did you catch it?

18:39.148 --> 18:42.031
Jesus claims to be bred that came down from heaven.

18:42.051 --> 18:43.632
Okay, okay, okay.

18:44.313 --> 18:46.215
The implication, I can hear the crowd talking is this.

18:46.295 --> 18:47.876
Are you claiming to be better than us, Jesus?

18:48.037 --> 18:49.578
Are you claiming to know God more than us?

18:49.658 --> 18:50.259
No, no, hold on.

18:50.599 --> 18:52.381
You're claiming you came from heaven.

18:52.721 --> 18:56.024
That means you actually are from not here and you're equal with God.

18:56.345 --> 18:57.726
Listen, you need to sit down, Jesus.

18:59.107 --> 19:00.809
We know you're special, but this is us.

19:00.829 --> 19:01.730
This is inappropriate.

19:02.110 --> 19:02.931
